update.description: The `LocalCache` can already return the path to the root of a cached model. This pull request adds the ability to get the local path to a model resource file, such as a mesh or a texture. This is important because Gazebo looks for resources independently of each other.
update.title: Get cached model resource file

content.raw:
Added a note in 02c4753. Did some investigating:

* Server API is currently always defaulting to `1.0`
* We're not getting it in the `config.yaml` file
* Do we want `ign-fuel-tools` to handle different `ign-fuelserver` APIs side-by-side? If not, then I propose removing the API version as a member of `ServerConfig` and moving it to a global configuration of fuel-tools.
content.html:
Added a note in 02c4753. Did some investigating:

  • Server API is currently always defaulting to 1.0
  • We're not getting it in the config.yaml file
  • Do we want ign-fuel-tools to handle different ign-fuelserver APIs side-by-side? If not, then I propose removing the API version as a member of ServerConfig and moving it to a global configuration of fuel-tools.

content.raw:
Merged pull request #65 into this one, please review that one first. Also cleaned the regex here in  a260c05.

Now the model file URL requires a model version, since that's the requirement on ign-fuel-server, i.e.:

* works: https://staging-api.ignitionfuel.org/1.0/chapulina/models/Custom%20drill/tip/files/meshes/cordless_drill.dae
* doesn't work: https://staging-api.ignitionfuel.org/1.0/chapulina/models/Custom%20drill/files/meshes/cordless_drill.dae
